## Security OS (`.ai.soc/`)

**Lost on security?** `.ai.soc/START_HERE.md` · **Router:** `@soc-director - <what you want>`

### SOC source resolution (thin-client)

SOC_SOURCE=REPLACE_SOCSOURCE

The agent MUST resolve `.ai.soc/` references from `$SOC_SOURCE` (thin-client mode). When `SOC_SOURCE` is set and readable, read `.ai.soc/skills/<id>/skill.md` from `$SOC_SOURCE/skills/<id>/skill.md`. Skills, standards, concepts, templates, and scripts resolve from the source at runtime.

### SOC context files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `.ai.soc/START_HERE.md` | Decision tree |
| `.work.soc/context/HANDOFF_SOC.md` | Session handoff |
| `.work.soc/plans/NEXT_SOC.md` | Tactical next action |
| `.work.soc/plans/UNKNOWNS_SOC.md` | Open unknowns |

### SOC placeholders

| Placeholder | Resolves to |
|-------------|-------------|
| `{WORK_SOC_ROOT}` | `.work.soc/` |
| `{HANDOFF_SOC}` | `.work.soc/context/HANDOFF_SOC.md` |
| `{NEXT_SOC}` | `.work.soc/plans/NEXT_SOC.md` |
| `{UNKNOWNS_SOC}` | `.work.soc/plans/UNKNOWNS_SOC.md` |
| `{SKILLS_SOC_ROOT}` | `$SOC_SOURCE/skills/` (from SOC_SOURCE pointer) |

### SOC skills

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| deploy-basic | Bootstrap `.work.soc/` + SOC source pointer (thin-client) |
| deploy-files | Copy `.ai.soc/` files into target (fat-client) |
| deploy-repo | Clone or archive the full `.ai.soc` repo |
| session-soc | SOC session bookend; start/close/status/context |
| soc-director | Run penetration tests against targets |
| soc-gateway | Run .ai.soc from source without system install |

**Sessions:** `@session-soc` — opens and closes SOC sessions

